               <head><!--no document type-->Hadleigh; 24 Elizabeth (1581-1582)</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="en">English</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> Indenture by which <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Rolfe</surname> of <orgName role="person" key="org_105021">Grey's Inne, Middlesex</orgName>, gent.</persName>, 
                  son and heir of <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> 
                           <surname>Rolfe</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_105321">Hadleigh (Hadley)</placeName>
                        </persName>, deceased, approves and ratifies to
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Atkinson</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_105321">Hadleigh (Hadley)</placeName>
                        </persName> 
                  all right and title to a capital mansion, &amp;c. in <placeName key="place_105321">Hadleigh (Hadley)</placeName>, which the said 
                  Thomas purchased of him and <persName>
                           <forename>Edward</forename> 
                           <surname>Colman</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_105311">Great Waldingfield</placeName>
                        </persName>.
                  Dated 28 October, <origDate notBefore="1581-11-17" notAfter="1582-11-16">24 Elizabeth</origDate>. 
                  
                  </p>
